cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture, which involves mixing features from different FPNs, indicating that it may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the performance of detectors, which may fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the MS-COCO benchmark, which is a widely used dataset in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
